This directory contains example programs that demonstrate how to 
use the IndigoVideo library.

File		Topics covered
----		--------------
burstcapt.c	burst capture of frames, GL display
chromamap.c	chroma key map
contcapt.c	continuous frame capture, GL display
oneframe.c	one frame capture, GL display
rgbgrab.c	live video input, one frame capture, GL display
simplegl.c	live video input in GL window, GL video event handling
simpleinput.c	live video input in GL window
sizeinput.c	live video input in GL window, GL event handling
svtomovie.c	burst capture of frames, movie file creation
vbounce.c	live video input in GL window
vclock.c	live video input in underlay, GL graphics
vgrab.c		one frame capture, live video input, GL display,
		SGI image file creation
vmirror.c	continuous frame capture, GL display, simple image manipulation
vnurbtex.c	continuous frame capture, GL display, simple image manipulation
vout.c		live video output
voverlay.c	live video input in overlay, GL graphics
vpaste.c	SGI image file to video output
xevents.c	live video input in X11 window, X11 video event handling
xrgbgrab.c	live video input in X11 window, one frame capture, X11 display


The following programs are shipped as executables in /usr/demos/bin:
vbounce, vclock, vmirror
